Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion Shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a garlic press).

Boil your #kettle{}, then pour the @Boiled Water for the Stock{500%milliliter} into a #measuring jug{} with the @Vegetable Stock Paste{20%grams}. Stir well to combine - this is your veg stock.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat.

> If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%grams}(diced) and shallot until the shallot has softened, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir in the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%grams} and @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet} and cook for ~{1%min} more. Add the @Risotto Rice{175%grams}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Stir your veg stock into the rice and mix to combine. Add the @Cherry Tomatoes{125%grams} and bring back to the boil.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the stock has been absorbed, ~{20-25%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%grams}.

While the risotto bakes, halve the @Lemon{1/2} (see ingredients for the amount) and squeeze the lemon juice into a large #bowl{}.

Add the @Sugar for the Dressing{1%tsp} and @Olive Oil for the Dressing{1%tbsp} to the bowl and mix together. Set aside.

When the risotto is ready, remove it from the oven and mix in the @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%grams}, a squeeze of lemon, @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%grams} and a knob of @?butter{} (if you have any).

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Add the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams} to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Share the risotto between your plates or #bowls{} and serve with the salad alongside. Sprinkle over the grated Cheddar to finish.

Enjoy!